orkshire, England"},"en":{"1430–":"1430–Deceased","1435–Female":"1435–Deceased","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1430–Male":"1430–Deceased","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1549":"1549","Holme in Spalding Moore, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England","Holme upon Spalding Moor, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Millington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the places in Cheshire and East Yorkshire. The Cheshire placename derives from Old English <i>mylen</i> ‘mill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The Yorkshire placename probably derives from an Old English personal name <i>Milla</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":25,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705201,"age":119,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Millington was born in 1430, in Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. William Millington."},"et":{"1430–":"1430–Surnud","1435–Female":"1435–Surnud","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1549":"1549","Holme in Spalding Moore, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England","Holme upon Spalding Moor, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1430–":"1430–Kuollut","1435–Female":"1435–Kuollut","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1549":"1549","Holme in Spalding Moore, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England","Holme upon Spalding Moor, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1430–":"1430–Décédé","1435–Female":"1435–Décédée","1460–1508":"1460–1508","1430–Male":"1430–Décédé","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1508":"1508","1549":"1549","Holme in Spalding Moore, Yorkshire, England":"Holme-on-Spalding-Moor, Everwyck, Angleterre","H